The paper deals with graphical models for multi-armed bandit problems, which are commonly studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and graph structures, which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
